\ group-by ( rows col -- { value -> set-of-rows } ): group an array of frames by a
\ symbol column. Buckets are sets (identical rows dedup); keys are the distinct
\ values, sorted; the column value must be a symbol.

\ === basic grouping ===
[ { :id 1 :cat :x } { :id 2 :cat :y } { :id 3 :cat :x } { :id 4 :cat :y } { :id 5 :cat :z } ] :cat group-by
dup keys . cr                                  \ the distinct values, sorted
dup :x @ size . cr                             \ 2
dup :y @ size . cr                             \ 2
:z @ size . cr                                 \ 1

\ === empty input -> empty frame ===
[ ] :cat group-by size . cr                    \ 0

\ === one value, distinct rows -> a single group holding all of them ===
[ { :id 1 :g :a } { :id 2 :g :a } { :id 3 :g :a } ] :g group-by
dup keys . cr                                  \ [ :a ]
:a @ size . cr                                 \ 3

\ === identical rows dedup within a bucket (buckets are sets) ===
[ { :id 1 :g :a } { :id 1 :g :a } { :id 2 :g :a } ] :g group-by :a @ size . cr   \ 2

\ === all-distinct values -> one bucket each ===
[ { :v :a } { :v :b } { :v :c } ] :v group-by keys size . cr   \ 3

\ === aggregation: group, then map each bucket to its size (count per group) ===
[ { :id 1 :c :x } { :id 2 :c :y } { :id 3 :c :x } { :id 4 :c :x } ] :c group-by values [: size :] map . cr   \ count per group: x->3, y->1

\ === a non-symbol column is rejected ===
[ { :id 1 } ] 5 group-by
bye
